<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-12-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-12-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="528" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d528">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 <gloss target="#t_EW1">EW</gloss> 1939/2057½</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President</gloss> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi><note n="1" xml:id="d528fn1">A paraphrase of this memorandum was cabled by
                                    <persName corresp="#p_HC1">Hull</persName> to <persName corresp="#p_WJG1">Winant</persName> on December 24,
                            1943.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-12-23">December 23, 1943</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p rend="center"><hi rend="smallcaps">Memorandum for the Secretary of
                                State</hi></p>
                        <p>This<note n="2" xml:id="d528fn2">The matter referred to in the preceding
                                document.</note> I think should be taken up by <persName corresp="#p_WJG1">Winant</persName> with Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_CC2">Churchill</persName> as soon as the latter gets
                            back. It was not brought up in any way at Teheran in my presence.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_RFD1">F. D.
                            R.</persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>